# API & Server Action Modification Guidelines

## Core Requirements
1. **Impact Analysis**: When modifying a Route Handler (`app/api/`) or a Server Action, check all frontend components that invoke them.
2. **Documentation**: Update API documentation or internal docs if the signature or return type changes.

## Checklist
- [ ] Verify frontend components and hooks that consume the API/Action.
- [ ] Update TypeScript types/interfaces shared between server and client.
- [ ] Ensure Server Actions handle errors gracefully and return actionable feedback.
- [ ] Check if documentation needs updates for modified endpoints.
- [ ] Run type-checking (`npx tsc --noEmit`) to catch broken references.
